[h1]v2.2 — The Reshape Update[/h1]

Built almost entirely from your feedback. Thank you — keep it coming.

[h2]Restyle anything. Keep it forever.[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]New styling UI for everyone[/b] — Ideology no longer required. Select the avatar and hit [i]restyle[/i]: live hologram preview, every hairstyle in the game, color swatches plus full RGB sliders.
[*][b]Gender toggle[/b] — project a male avatar; every announcement and chat log follows with the right pronouns. Standard build tracks the toggle automatically.
[*][b]Body types[/b] — Standard, Thin, Fat, Hulk... and modded body types appear automatically.
[*][b]Face selection[/b] — choose from every head type for the chosen gender. Modded face/head packs slot straight into the grid, no patch needed.
[*][b]Your customization now persists[/b] — restyles survive persona swaps, saves, and gravship launches. Swap to I.X.I.A. for a prison week and your custom P.R.I.S.M. is exactly as you left her when you return. This was the big one — fixed for hair AND the new appearance options.
[/list]

[h2]Fixes[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]"She won't use my doors!"[/b] — fixed. The avatar now phases through every door at every level of the pathing system, including locked doors and modded door types. No more standing-error spam at the brig threshold.
[*][b]Summon now teleports — and only to your own deck.[/b] No more ordering her on a hike across the map; illegal targets are rejected outright, and legal ones flicker her straight there.
[*][b]Off-ship spawning[/b] — a holocore built against the hull could project the avatar onto the dirt outside. Projection now always lands on your gravship's substructure.
[*]The holocore no longer offers its janky rotation option — the console face always reads south.
[*]Cancelling the styling screen properly reverts every change (and the old bug where opening it stripped the hair color is gone for good).
[/list]

[h2]Flavor[/h2]
[list]
[*]Every persona now announces herself when she materializes, in her own voice. P.R.I.S.M. counted the seconds while she was away. The Crimson Warden RETURNS. O-hohohoho.
[/list]

[i]Save-compatible with existing games. Ideology owners lose nothing — the new styling UI does everything the old station dialog did and more.[/i]
